  <h1>Purified Ore</h1>
  <h3>Source</h3>
  <text>
    <style color="0xaaaaaa" italic="true">Note: this page is ported from MCMOD's GTCEu wiki.<br></br>Author: <style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://center.mcmod.cn/119280/">Oganesson897</style>, <br></br><style color="0xa4e7ff" hover-info="url" underlined="true" url-link="https://github.com/blackdragon2447">BlackDragon2447</style><br></br></style>
  </text>
  <text>
	  <style color="0xaaaaaa">(Purified ore is an intermediary product in the processing of ores, see the ore processing tab in JEI/REI/EMI for any ore's specific processing steps)</style>
  </text>
  <br/>
  <text>
	Crushed ore is obtained by processing <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:materials/crushed_ore" underlined="true">Crushed Ore</style> 
	in a  <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/ore_wahser" underlined="true">Ore Washer</style>
	or, for some ores, a <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/chemical_bath" underlined="true">Chemical Bath</style>, where both 
	processes yield diffiernt byproducts. Purified ore can be further processed into <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:materials/purified_dust" underlined="true">Purified Dust</style>
	using a <style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/macerator" underlined="true">Macerator</style> or
	<style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/forge_hammer" underlined="true">Forge Hammer</style> or into 
	<style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:materials/refined_ore" underlined="true">Refined Ore</style> in a 
	<style color="0xafff00" hover-info="click link" link="gtceu:machines/thermal_centrifuge" underlined="true">Thermal Centrifuge</style>.
  </text>
